      <p>First, could I again quickly draw attention to this bug: <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1344525" rel="nofollow">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1344525</a> . It&#8217;s a very serious issue with images (and other replaced content) in Grid layout that also appears to affect Chrome, it can only be hackishly fixed with JavaScript, and it runs the risk of becoming the locked in behaviour if it&#8217;s not fixed soon.</p>
